                            While sustainable architecture requires thoughtful planning and sometimes higher upfront
                            costs, the long-term financial benefits are substantial:
                        </p>

                        <ol>
                            <li>Reduced energy bills through improved efficiency</li>
                            <li>Higher property values and increased marketability</li>
                            <li>Lower maintenance costs with durable, quality materials</li>
                            <li>Tax incentives and rebates for green building features</li>
                            <li>Protection against rising energy costs</li>
                        </ol>

                        <h2>Looking Ahead: The Future is Green</h2>

